 MOUKA has donated 100 Klinic Hospital Mattresses and 30 cartons of its insect repellent, Mouka Mozzi, to the Oyo State Government for its isolation centres. Chief Commercial Officer Dimeji Osingunwa said Nigerians’ well-being was at the core of the company’s mission. He said the mattresses were designed for medical use, with a waterproof cover to protect them from contamination and a firm foam core to keep patients comfortable. Commissioner for Finance Akinola Ojo said the mattresses would help to boost the facilities at the isolation centres. He noted that the state government was taking giant strides in ensuring quick recovery of infected persons.